    <h2>Biography</h2>

    <p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kevin-heuzey/" target="_blank">Kevin Heuzey</a> is an Israeli tech entrepreneur, crypto infrastructure architect, and the founder of <a href="https://www.integrity.farm" target="_blank">Integrity.farm</a> — a blockchain protocol that redefines Bitcoin mining through <em>on-chain emulation</em>.</p>

    <p>In <strong>2015</strong>, Heuzey launched <strong>Ethereum Garden</strong>, built from scratch in <strong>Odessa, Ukraine</strong>. The project scaled to over 2,500 GPUs and was profiled by <a href="https://telegraf.com.ua/ukr/statti/2018-05-30/5911124-ethereum-garden-naysmilivishiy-mayning-proekt-skhidnoi-evropi" target="_blank">Telegraf</a><sup>[1]</sup>.</p>

    <p>In <strong>2016</strong>, he joined the <a href="https://www.timesofisrael.com/situation-gets-hackathoner-to-make-riot-warning-app/" target="_blank">Israel Tech Challenge</a><sup>[2]</sup>, where he studied AI, blockchain, and cybersecurity with <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unit_8200" target="_blank">Unit 8200</a> alumni.</p>

    <p>In <strong>2017</strong>, he worked with <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/wolodymyrt/" target="_blank">Volodymyr Taratushka</a> of <a href="https://hacken.io" target="_blank">Hacken</a>, advising HackIT and serving as a jury member at the <a href="https://ctftime.org/event/672/" target="_blank">HackIT Cup</a><sup>[3]</sup> — an event supported by <a href="https://fenbushi.vc" target="_blank">Fenbushi Capital</a><sup>[4]</sup> and attended by <a href="https://vitalik.eth.limo" target="_blank">Vitalik Buterin</a>.</p>

    <p>In <strong>2018</strong>, he contributed to HackIT events alongside <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phil_Zimmermann" target="_blank">Phil Zimmermann</a><sup>[5]</sup> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Wozniak" target="_blank">Steve Wozniak</a>.</p>

    <p>In <strong>December 2017</strong>, he led the construction of a 2.5 MW Tier 4 Bitcoin mining facility at the <a href="https://www.bell-labs.com/" target="_blank">Nokia Paris-Saclay campus</a><sup>[6]</sup>, which became the Blockchain Research Institute.</p>

    <p>In <strong>2024</strong>, <a href="https://www.vistory.com" target="_blank">Vistory</a> became seed investor of Integrity.farm and helped build its core protocol, alongside its work on <a href="https://www.eurosatory.com/en/innovations/mainchain/" target="_blank">MainChain</a><sup>[7]</sup>.</p>

    <p>Today, Kevin focuses on designing verifiable, trustless infrastructure bridging energy systems and on-chain incentives. He writes regularly about Web3 architecture, Bitcoin mining economics, and zero-knowledge systems.</p>

    <p>More at <a href="https://kevinheuzey.com" target="_blank">kevinheuzey.com</a> and <a href="https://www.integrity.farm" target="_blank">integrity.farm</a>.</p>

